&lt;Besicorp Group Inc> said itreached an agreement with &lt;LCP Chemicals and Plastics Inc> todevelop an 80 megawatt cogeneration station at LCP's facilityin Syracuse N.Y., in a project estimated to require about 50mln dlrs in financing.    Under the agreement, it said a standard power saleagreement is expected to be entered into with Niagara MohawkPower Corp &lt;NMK> for the sale of electrical power output.    Besicrop said it is developing the project with &lt;KamineEngineering and Mechanical Contracting &lt;Inc>, and bothcompanies will retain long-term interests in the project. Reuter&#3;